    "text": "Act to exempt religious Members and Individuals from Social Security and Healthcare taxes Act or the AMISH Act\n\nThis bill allows an employee, based on a conscientious, faith based objection, to apply for a credit or refund of deductions from that employee's wages for Social Security and Medicare taxes, provided that the employee waives all related federal benefits thereto."
